ms) before affecting the decision. The smaller the percentage, the more sensitive the decision is to that variable. Sensitivity % = Profit/Variable  [Data: Concepts (3)]\"\n        }}\n    ]\n}}\n\n# Real Data\n\nUse the following text for your answer. Do not make anything up in your answer.\n\nText:\n-----Entities-----\nhuman_readable_id,title,description,degree\n850,\"\"\"HIGH-LOW METHOD\"\"\",\"The High-Low Method is a technique used to calculate costs by analyzing the highest and lowest levels of activity and their associated costs. It is employed to estimate the fixed and variable components of a cost by examining these extreme activity levels and their corresponding costs. This method involves selecting the costs associated with the highest and lowest levels of activity and assuming a straight-line relationship between these two points. By doing so, it helps in estimating the fixed and variable elements of a semi-variable cost, enabling more accurate forecasts of costs. Specifically, the High-Low Method calculates the variable overhead cost per unit by taking the difference in costs at the highest and lowest levels of activity and dividing it by the difference in activity levels.\",8\n864,\"\"\"QUIZ: COST\"\"\",\"\"\"This quiz involves questions related to cost analysis and budgeting techniques.\"\"\",5\n859,\"\"\"CORRELATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Correlation\"\" is an analysis technique used to measure the strength and direction of the relationship between two variables. It refers to the closeness of the relationship between two or more variables and can be positive, negative, perfect, or zero, indicating the degree to which variables move together.\",4\n860,\"\"\"REGRESSION\"\"\",\"\"\"Regression\"\" is an analysis technique used to model the relationship between a dependent variable and one or more independent variables. Specifically, regression analysis is used to forecast the value of one variable based on the value of another by assuming a linear relationship described by the equation y = a + bx. The values of a and b in this equation can be determined using the least squares regression method.\",4\n861,\"\"\"TIME SERIES ANALYSIS\"\"\",\"\"\"Time series analysis\"\" involves analyzing data points collected or recorded at specific time intervals to identify trends, cycles, and seasonal variations. It can be applied to any figures that vary over time, including sales, production, and costs. The main components of a time series are trend, seasonal variations, cyclical variations, and random variations.\",4\n2177,\"\"\"ESTIMATION OF FIXED AND VARIABLE ELECTRICITY COSTS USING THE HIGH-LOW METHOD\"\"\",\"\"\"Tomkins Co uses the High-Low Method to estimate the fixed and variable components of electricity costs based on direct labour hours, helping to prepare a flexible budget for the upcoming year.\"\"\",1\n867,\"\"\"HIGH-LOW METHOD QUIZ\"\"\",\"\"\"The High-Low Method Quiz involves calculating the estimated maintenance cost for production of a battery at 80% of maximum demand, using historical machine hours and maintenance costs data.\"\"\",1\n868,\"\"\"TREND\"\"\",\"\"\"Trend refers to the underlying long-term movement in values over time.\"\"\",2\n882,\"\"\"TYPES OF CORRELATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Types of Correlation include positive correlation (both variables increase together), negative correlation (one variable increases while the other decreases), perfect correlation (a change in one variable is matched by an equal change in the other), and zero correlation (no relationship between variables).\"\"\",1\n891,\"\"\"REGRESSION FORMULAE\"\"\",\"\"\"The formulae for calculating the regression coefficients are: a = \u03a3y/n - b\u03a3x/n and b = (n\u03a3xy - \u03a3x\u03a3y)/(n\u03a3x^2 - (\u03a3x)^2). These formulae help determine the line of best fit for the data.\"\"\",1\n869,\"\"\"EXAMPLE OF TREND\"\"\",\"\"\"This example shows sales data of three products (Red, Blue, and Green) over several years, illustrating different trends: a dow